==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ambulance
<hw>Am"bu*lance</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ambulance</ets>, h⟦ocir⟧pital <ets>ambulant</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>ambulare</ets> to walk. See <er>Amble</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A field hospital, so organized as to
follow an army in its movements, and intended to succor the wounded as
soon as possible. Often used adjectively; <as>as, an <ex>ambulance</ex>
wagon; <ex>ambulance</ex> stretcher; <ex>ambulance</ex>
corps.</as></def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An ambulance wagon or cart for
conveying the wounded from the field, or to a hospital.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambulant</ent>⟦br⟧
